enhanced_by.reason: The mapIterator method relies on the initialization of the delegate Trie, which is set up in the unmodifiableTrie method.
The mapIterator method wraps the delegate's iterator with an unmodifiable iterator, similar to how the unmodifiableOrderedMapIterator method wraps an iterator.

The mapIterator method returns an iterator over the entries of the Trie, similar to the entrySet method which returns a set of entries. Assertions can be made about the contents of the iterator based on the entries returned by entrySet.
The mapIterator method iterates over keys and values, and the keySet method returns a set of keys. Assertions can be made about the keys returned by the iterator based on the keys returned by keySet.
